Detailed Description

Formal protocol for an object which can contain Starks in a managed object context, and has a Starker available.

Conforming classes will provide methods to

Access the Starker (of course!) Answer questions regarding placing additional Starks in the receiver Identify the class's Browfile (optional)

This protocol was established to express the commonality between the internal representation of Starks in a Bookshelf and their external representation in an Extore. Bookshelf and Extore adopt this protocol.

Member Function Documentation

- (Browfile*) browfile   [optional]

Gets the receiver's browfile.

This method is optional because Extore subclasses will have a browfile but Bookshelf objects will not.

Returns:
The receiver's browfile

- (BOOL) canBeAtRootStark: (Stark *)  stark  

Tests whether or not a given Stark can be inserted as a child of the root item in the receiver.

Depends on the browser or service.

Parameters:
stark The Stark to be tested
Returns:
YES if OK to insert, NO if not.

- (BkmxHas) hasBar  

Returns whether or not the receiver's ownerApp has a permanent collection called a "Bookmarks Bar", "Bookmarks Toolbar" or equivalent.

Returns:
Returns BkmxHasExplicit If it has an explicit Bookmarks Bar with children not repeated in other collections. Returns BkmxHasSmart if it creates a Bookmarks Bar dynamically by copying items in other collections which have some kind of Bookmarks Bar "flag". Returns BkmxHasNot if receiver's ownerApp has no kind of Bookmarks Bar whatsoever are stored

- (BOOL) hasOhared  

Returns whether or not the receiver's ownerApp has a permanent collection designated for "Shared" bookmarks.

Do not confuse this with the capacity of a web service external store to set individual bookmarks "shared" or "private".

- (Stark*) starkFromExternalPlistNode: (NSDictionary *)  item  

Returns a new stark modelling a given item from the external store.

Subclasses must override. Default implementation logs an Internal Error and returns nil.

Parameters:
item The item from the external store to be modelled.
Returns:
The new stark
